{
  "doc_id": "16303",
  "text": "A direct nested PCR strategy targeting the 18s-rRNA gene using the Blood Phusion Direct PCR Kit (Thermo Scientific, Waltham, MA) as described by Fuehrer et al. [CITATION_1] was followed with modifications (Table 1) . For the nest1 protocol, a total master-mix volume of 25 µL was added directly to the wells containing blood spots (Fig. 1 , Table 1 ). After nest1 completion, the microplate was centrifuged at room temperature at 1000 G for 3 min. 3 µL of nest1 PCR product were transferred to a new microplate in order to perform the nest2 reaction (Fig. 1, Table 1 ) with a final volume of 20 µL. Nest2 PCR products were analysed by gel electrophoresis in a 1.5 % agarose gel stained with ethidium bromide (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO).",
